cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of semantic segmentation in medical imaging, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The study involves analyzing the effect of label errors on model performance, which is a key concern in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning architectures such as U-Net, SegNet, and FCN32 also suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Finally, the study involves training models for liver segmentation, which is a specific medical imaging task that could fall under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE).
